Description: Salmonella paratyphi clyA gene for cytolysin A.
Organism :  Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Paratyphi A
Accession Number : AJ313033.1

Cytolysin A (ClyA) is a pore-forming cytotoxic protein encoded by the clyA gene, characterized so far only in Escherichia coli (E. coli). 
It is conserved in the human-specific typhoid Salmonella enterica serovars Typhi and Paratyphi.
The entire clyA gene locus is absent in many other S. enterica serovars, including Typhimurium. 
